lspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"|[[Korean Service Medal]] w/ two [[Service star|{{frac|3|16}}\" bronze stars]]\n|colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"|[[Vietnam Service Medal]] w/ three {{frac|3|16}}\" silver stars and one {{frac|3|16}}\" bronze star\n|colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"|[[United Nations Korea Medal]]\n|colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"|[[Republic of Vietnam Campaign Medal]] w/ 1960- device\n|-\n|}\n</center>\n\n==Other awards and honors==\n\n* 1990: Johnson was inducted into the [[Woodrow Wilson High School (Dallas)|Woodrow Wilson High School]] Hall of Fame.\n* October 2009: the Congressional Medal of Honor Society awarded Johnson the National Patriot Award, the Society's highest civilian award given to Americans who exemplify patriotism and strive to better the nation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dallasnews.com/sharedcontent/dws/news/politics/state/stories/DN-johnsonmedal_03met.ART.State.Edition1.4bee69b.html |title=Congressional Medal of Honor Society selects Sam Johnson for its National Patriot Award &#124; News for Dallas, Texas &#124; Dallas Morning News &#124; Texas Politics &#124; The Dallas Morning News |publisher=Dallasnews.com |date=2009-10-03 |accessdate=2010-08-29}}</ref>\n* 2011: Freedom of Flight award<ref>[https://www.gop.gov/member/sam-johnson/ House Republicans]</ref>\n* March 2016: Congressional Patriots Award<ref>[http://samjohnson.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=398188]</ref>\n*April 2016: Patriot Award<ref>[http://starlocalmedia.com/friscoenterprise/u-s-rep-sam-johnson-honored-with-patriot-award-at/article_731ad6f8-1082-11e6-a0e2-27e862092c13.html]</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n* 1992, ''Captive Warriors: A Vietnam P.O.W.'s Story''; ISBN 0-89096-496-3\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Korean War veterans who are recipients of the Bronze Star]]\n\n{{Portalbar|Texas|Politics|United States Air Force|Methodism}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.samjohnson.house.gov/ Congressman Sam Johnson] official House si